Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person or entity ("User") obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation files (the "Software"), to use, copy, modify, and distribute the Software for the purposes described herein, subject to the following conditions:

1. Purpose: The Software, "CyborgBulls Scouting," is intended to facilitate scouting of teams during FIRST Robotics Competition (FRC) events for the CyborgBulls team. It is designed to simplify scouting processes and enhance team performance during competitions.

2. Authorized Users: The Software may be used by teams participating in FRC events who have explicitly requested access, as well as by contributors to the associated GitHub repository. Additionally, beginner French FRC teams seeking assistance in getting started are also authorized users of the Software.

3. Limitations on Use: Any use of the Software outside the scope of FRC events is strictly prohibited, except for events directly related to FRC, such as white kickoff events.

4. Distribution: The Software is currently distributed free of charge. Any potential future paid distribution will be at the discretion of Crazzynel Devs.

5. Transparency and Security: The Software is open source, allowing knowledgeable users to contribute to its improvement. However, users are cautioned against any misuse or unauthorized modification of the Software that could compromise security or violate the intended purpose of the application.

6. Disclaimer of Liability: Crazzynel Devs and associated contributors disclaim any responsibility for issues or damages arising from the use of the Software. The application cannot be reliably traced, and users are advised to exercise caution when using the Software.

7. Enforcement: Crazzynel Devs reserves the right to pursue legal action or revoke licenses in cases of misuse or unethical use of the Software.

By using the Software, Users agree to abide by the terms and conditions set forth in this license.
